    "plan_content": "Here's the complete implementation plan:\n\n---\n\n## Plan: `Bun.INI` Namespace\n\n### Key Finding\n**An INI parser already exists** in `src/ini.zig`. The `Parser` struct handles sections, key=value pairs, and `;`/`#` comment lines. The `IniTestingAPIs.parse()` function at line 674 is the direct template for the public parse binding. Only `stringify` needs to be written from scratch.\n\n### 7 Changes Required\n\n| # | File | Change |\n|---|------|--------|\n| 1 | **`src/bun.js/api/INIObject.zig`** | **NEW** — `create()`, `parse()` (wraps `ini.Parser`), `stringify()` |\n| 2 | `src/bun.js/api.zig` | `pub const INIObject = @import(\"./api/INIObject.zig\");` |\n| 3 | `src/bun.js/api/BunObject.zig` | 4 sub-edits: lazy prop, getter fn, `@export`, import alias |\n| 4 | `src/bun.js/bindings/BunObject+exports.h` | `macro(INI) \\` in `FOR_EACH_GETTER` (alphabetically between `Glob` and `JSON5`) |\n| 5 | `src/bun.js/bindings/BunObject.cpp` | Add `INI   BunObject_lazyPropCb_wrap_INI   DontDelete|PropertyCallback` row |\n| 6 | `packages/bun-types/bun.d.ts` | `namespace INI { parse, stringify }` |\n| 7 | **`test/js/bun/ini/ini-public-api.test.ts`** | **NEW** — test file |\n\n### Parse Implementation\nDirectly reuse `ini.Parser.init()` → `parser.parse()` → `parser.out.toJS()` (same as `IniTestingAPIs.parse()`).\n\n### Stringify Algorithm\nTwo-pass JSPropertyIterator walk: (1) emit scalar top-level values as `key=value\\n`; (2) emit object-valued top-level keys as `\\n[section]\\n` + their key-value pairs. Return as JS string.\n\n### Verification\n`bun run build` → `bun bd test test/js/bun/ini/ini-public-api.test.ts` → `bun bd test test/js/bun/ini/ini.test.ts`",
